translated_Romanian_English: I ordered 4 products, two of which did not fit in size. I consulted a "sportsman" and following the instructions (the products were sent through Fan Curier, I included a note with clear specifications for the products I wanted) I returned the products. It's been 6 days and I haven't received any sign from Decathlon, which led me to call them. The person I spoke to told me to be patient, probably the package hadn't arrived (it's quite curious that the package didn't arrive in 6 days). The next day, I called Decathlon again, where the person I spoke to assured me that the package had arrived and the next day it would be sent back to me with the requested products since they had just received the goods. Four more days have passed and I called again, where a female staff member, after my insistence, looked for the package, said she found it but didn't have one of the products. Please explain to me why the return took so long and why I wasn't notified. If you're a serious company, I think I deserve at least an explanation.
translated_English_Chinese: 我订购了4件产品，其中两件大小不合适。我咨询了一位“运动员”，并按照说明（产品通过Fan Curier送达，我附上了对所需产品的明确规格的注释）退回了产品。已经过去6天了，但我没有收到来自Decathlon的任何通知，这让我不得不打电话给他们。我跟客服人员通话后，被告知要有耐心，可能包裹还没到（令人好奇的是，包裹在6天内尚未到达）。第二天，我又致电Decathlon，对方人员告诉我包裹已经收到，并且由于刚刚收到货物，第二天就会将所需产品送回给我。又过去了4天，我再次打电话，客服人员在我的坚持下找到了包裹，说找到了，但其中一个产品没有。如果你们是一家认真的公司，我认为至少应该给我一个解释，说明为什么退货花了这么长时间，以及为什么我没有收到通知。
translated_Chinese_Romanian: Am comandat 4 produse, dintre care două erau de mărime inadecvată. M-am consultat cu un „sportiv” și am returnat produsele conform instrucțiunilor (produsele au fost livrate prin Fan Curier, la care am atașat o notă cu specificații clare despre produsele necesare). Au trecut deja 6 zile, dar nu am primit nicio notificare din partea Decathlon, ceea ce m-a obligat să îi sun. După ce am vorbit cu un reprezentant al serviciului clienți, mi s-a spus să fiu răbdător, că pachetul nu a ajuns încă (ceva curios, având în vedere că pachetul nu a ajuns în 6 zile). A doua zi, l-am sunat din nou pe Decathlon și persoana cu care am vorbit mi-a spus că pachetul a fost primit și, deoarece abia primiseră marfa, îmi va trimite produsele necesare a doua zi. Au trecut alte 4 zile, iar eu l-am sunat din nou, iar reprezentantul serviciului clienți, după insistențele mele, a găsit pachetul și mi-a spus că l-a găsit, dar lipsește un produs. Dacă sunteți o companie serioasă, consider că ar trebui să-mi oferiți cel puțin o explicație pentru întârzierea la retur și lipsa notificărilor.

text: Am fost in magazinul din Baneasa imediat dupa deschidere si am intrebat la service cat dureaza service-ul complet al unei perechi de schiuri. Persoana responsabila mi-a comunicat 1-2 zile cel mult. Am venit a doua zi cu schiurile (6 IAN) si am cerut service complet, le-am lasat si mi-au comunicat ca ma suna ei cand sunt gata.Timp de o saptamana nu a sunat nimeni si am decis sa sun eu pentru a afla statusul. Mi-au spus ca sunt gata si ca le pot ridica. Am ajuns in magazin, si...schiurile erau ceruite si atat. Aceleasi gauri cu care le-am lasat, erau prezente pe talpi. A zis ca le repara pe loc. A aprins o bagheta de Cofix si a inceput sa aplice peste suprafata CERUITA. Schiurile inainte de a fi reparate se degreseaza din cate stiu eu, nu am putut sa ma abtin si i-am spun la final ca eu le fac cel putin la fel de bine in balcon, fara prea multe echipamente, precum le-a facut el. .Dupa ce a curatat excesul de Cofix, le-a slefuit si mi-au inapoiat schiurile. Nu era cazul cumva sa le ceruiasca la final?Cred ca au avut sificient timp o saptamana sa le analizeze si sa fie facute cum trebuie. Eu mi-am mai reparat echilament de schi in Decathlon si am fost foarte multumit pana acum, dar cei din Baneasa au dezamagit, poate ca era la inceput, poate prea aglomerati.

absa_target: service is positive; staff competency is negative
translated_Romanian_English: I was in the Baneasa store immediately after opening and asked the service staff how long a complete ski service takes. The person in charge told me 1-2 days at most. I came back the next day with my skis (January 6th) and requested a full service, left them there, and they told me they would call me when they're ready. For a week, no one called, so I decided to call to find out the status. They told me they were ready and that I could pick them up. I arrived at the store, and... my skis were waxed and that's it. The same holes I had left them with were still present on the bases. He said he would repair them on the spot. He lit a Cofix stick and started applying it over the WAXED surface. As far as I know, skis are degreased before being repaired, but I couldn't help myself and told him at the end that I can do at least as good of a job in my balcony with minimal equipment, just like he did. After cleaning up the excess Cofix, he sharpened them and returned my skis to me. Shouldn't they have been edges-tuned at the end? I think they had enough time - a week - to analyze and do the job properly. I've also had my ski bindings repaired in Decathlon before and was very satisfied until now, but the ones in Baneasa disappointed me; maybe it was because it was their first time or maybe they were too busy.
translated_English_Chinese: 我在Băneasa商店开业后立即前往，并询问服务人员完整的滑雪板维护需要多长时间。负责人告诉我最多1-2天。我第二天带着我的滑雪板（1月6日）回来，要求进行全面维护，将其留在那里，他们告诉我他们会在完成后打电话给我。一周过去了，没有人打来电话，所以我决定打电话询问状态。他们告诉我已经完成，可以取回。到达商店后，我的滑雪板仅仅被涂上蜡，底部仍然存在我留下的相同的孔。服务人员说他会立即修复。他点燃了一根Cofix火柴，并开始在已涂蜡的表面涂上修复剂。据我所知，在维修滑雪板之前需要进行去油处理，但我忍不住告诉他，我可以在阳台上使用最基本的设备做同样好的工作。清理掉多余的Cofix后，他磨利了滑雪板并将其归还给我。难道他们不应该在最后调节边缘吗？我想他们有足够的时间——一周——来分析和正确完成这项工作。我也曾在Decathlon维修过我的滑雪板绑带，直到现在都很满意，但Băneasa的商店让我感到失望；也许这是因为这是他们第一次尝试，或者他们太忙了。
translated_Chinese_Romanian: Am mers imediat la magazinul Băneasa după deschidere și am întrebat personalul despre timpul necesar pentru service-ul complet al schiurilor. Șeful mi-a spus că vor dura maxim 1-2 zile. A doua zi (6 ianuarie) am revenit cu schiurile mele și am cerut service complet, lăsându-le acolo, iar ei mi-au spus că mă vor suna după ce vor fi gata. O săptămână a trecut și nimeni nu m-a sunat, așa că am decis să-i sun pentru a întreba despre stadiul lucrărilor. Mi-au spus că sunt gata și pot fi ridicate. Când am ajuns la magazin, schiurile mele fuseseră doar unsă cu ceară, iar găurile de pe fund erau aceleași pe care le lăsasem eu. Personalul mi-a spus că va face reparațiile imediat. A aprins o chibrită Cofix și a început să pună material de reparat pe suprafața unsă cu ceară. Știam că înainte de reparații ar trebui făcut un tratament de curățare, dar nu am putut să-i spun că pot face același lucru și pe balconul meu, folosind echipamente de bază. După ce a curățat excesul de Cofix, a ascuțit schiurile și mi le-a dat înapoi. Nu ar fi trebuit să ajusteze marginile la final? Cred că aveau suficient timp - o săptămână - pentru a analiza și face corect lucrarea. Am mai reparat legăturile de schi la Decathlon și până acum sunt mulțumit, dar magazinul Băneasa m-a dezamăgit; poate era prima dată când încercau sau erau prea ocupați.

translated_Romanian_English: The staff lacked promptness. I purchased products from several sectors, and all employees were lacking the courtesy specific to retail workers. They were lacking enthusiasm, like they had no 'life' in them, moving slowly as if we bothered them. This is the first time I've experienced this in your store. Maybe they were new employees who didn't know the products very well, but this damages your company's image. Maybe you should hire people based on their competence and not physical appearance. I'm sorry I have nothing favorable to write.
translated_English_Chinese: 员工缺乏及时性，我从多个部门购买了产品，所有员工都缺乏特定于零售工人的礼貌，他们没有热情，就像他们没有'生命'一样，行动迟缓，好像我们打扰了他们。这是我第一次在您的商店里遇到这种情况。也许他们是新员工，不太了解产品，但这会损害贵公司的形象。也许您应该根据能力而不是外貌聘用人员。我抱歉，我没有什么好话可写。
translated_Chinese_Romanian: Lipsa de promptitud a angajaților, am cumpărat produse de la mai multe departamente, toți angajații au lipsit politeness specifică lucrătorilor din vânzări, nu aveau entuziasm, păreau că nu au „viață”, se mișcau lent, ca și cum ne-am fi deranjat. Acesta este primul meu caz în magazinele dvs. Poate că sunt angajați noi, care nu cunosc prea bine produsele, dar acest lucru va afecta imaginea companiei dvs. Poate că ar trebui să angajați oameni după capacități și nu după înfățișare. Îmi pare rău, nu am ceva deosebit de bun de spus.

text: I bought this mask as a backup, I require optical corrective lenses and can't be installed in it. It fits me perfectly I have a narrow bonny face and a big nose and most masks don't go well they leak near my nose (Mares X-Vision, Cressi Big Eyes). I was stunned by how clear the glass is and the quality of the silicone skirt (great material like liquid skin) generously added, just look at the under nose area, long enough to compensate large cheeks or facial hair. Wished my main mask had this high quality skirt. About the steaming up, it's quite normal for high end masks made out of tempered glass, just use anti fogging solution, gel or spray, I use cressi bioantifog gel, start by cleaning the inside glass with water, dry it with textile, pour 2-3 drops, spread the solution in a thin layer all over the glass, leave it for a minute, gently wash (just submerge it once or twice) with water and enjoy the next no fogging hours. You might consider spit instead of anti fogging solution and not required actually tooth brushing the glass to clear the protective fabrication silicone layer. If you wash it intensively after the treatment, or during swim the protection will wash away and you'll have to repeat the process. So keep the inside dry after treatment. And there's no reason to treat the outside part of the mask. So great product (by some a top 10 one) for a great price.

About the steaming up, it's quite normal for high end masks made out of tempered glass, just use anti fogging solution, gel or spray, I use cressi bioantifog gel, start by cleaning the inside glass with water, dry it with textile, pour 2-3 drops, spread the solution in a thin layer all over the glass, leave it for a minute, gently wash (just submerge it once or twice) with water and enjoy the next no fogging hours. You might consider spit instead of anti fogging solution and not required actually tooth brushing the glass to clear the protective fabrication silicone layer. If you wash it intensively after the treatment, or during swim the protection will wash away and you'll have to repeat the process. So keep the inside dry after treatment. And there's no reason to treat the outside part of the mask. So great product (by some a top 10 one) for a great price. </s>

translated_English_Chinese: 我购买了这个面罩作为备用，我需要光学矫正镜片，而不能安装在它上面。它非常适合我，我有一个狭窄的脸和一个大鼻子，大多数面罩不太适合，会在我的鼻子周围漏气（Mares X-Vision，Cressi Big Eyes）。我对玻璃的清晰度和硅胶边框的质量感到惊讶（像液体皮肤一样的优质材料），看看下面的鼻子区域，足够长，以弥补大脸颊或面部毛发。希望我的主要面罩有这样的高品质边框。关于起雾的问题，这是高端面罩使用钢化玻璃的正常现象，只需使用抗雾溶液、凝胶或喷雾，我使用Cressi Bioantifog Gel，先用水清洁内部玻璃，然后用纺织物擦干，再滴2-3滴，均匀地涂抹在整个玻璃上，等待一分钟，轻轻洗净（仅浸泡一次或两次）后，就可以享受几个小时的无雾状态。你可能会考虑使用口水而不是抗雾溶液，并不需要实际刷牙清除保护层硅胶。所以，如果你在处理后进行了强烈的清洗，或者在游泳过程中，保护层就会被冲走，你需要重复这个过程。因此，在处理后保持内部干燥是非常重要的。而且没有理由对面罩的外部进行处理。因此，这是一个很好的产品（有些人认为它是十大最佳产品之一），价格也非常合理。
translated_Chinese_Romanian: Am cumpărat această mască ca rezervă, deoarece am nevoie de lentile corective optice și nu pot să le montez pe ea. Îmi vine foarte bine, deoarece am o față îngustă și un nas mare, iar majoritatea măștilor nu se potrivesc prea bine și lasă aerul să iasă în jurul nasului (Mares X-Vision, Cressi Big Eyes). M-am mirat de claritatea sticlei și de calitatea marginilor din siliciu (un material de foarte bună calitate, ca o piele lichidă), uitați-vă la zona de sub nas, suficient de lungă pentru a compensa obrajii mari sau părul facial. Sper ca mască mea principală să aibă astfel de margini de înaltă calitate. Cu privire la problema aburirii, acesta este un fenomen normal pentru măștile de înaltă calitate cu sticlă temperată, doar trebuie să folosiți o soluție anti-abur, gel sau spray, eu folosesc Cressi Bioantifog Gel, mai întâi curăț interiorul sticlei cu apă, apoi șterg cu un material moale, apoi pun 2-3 picături și le aplic uniform pe toată sticla, aștept un minut, apoi spăl ușor (doar o dată sau de două ori) și pot savura câteva ore fără abur. Este posibil să luați în considerare folosirea salivei în loc de soluție anti-abur, nu este necesar să îndepărtați stratul protector de siliciu prin periaj. Deci, dacă faceți o spălare puternică după aplicare sau în timpul înotului, stratul protector va fi spălat și va trebui să repetați procesul. Prin urmare, este foarte important să păstrați interiorul uscat după aplicare. Și nu există niciun motiv să faceți o astfel de procedură pentru exteriorul măștii. Prin urmare, acesta este un produs foarte bun (unii o consideră una dintre cele mai bune zece), iar prețul este foarte rezonabil.

text: Termenul de 1 luna pentru inapoierea produselor mi se pare normal si corect doar pentru produsele pe care cumparatorul nu le mai doreste datorita culorii, marimii..sau pur si simplu. Pentru celelalte motive, gen scanare gresita sau articol defect, stricat, mi se pare termenul destul de mic si clar ar trebui marit la cel putin 3-6 luni. Daca cineva cumpara un cort in luna decembrie, e clar ca nu o sa il despacheteza de abia in luna mai-iunie. Daca are ghinionul sa fie defect, e mai complicat sa il schimbe. Se poate, deoarece stiu ca eu am patit, dar poate nu tot timpul este asa simplu. De asemenea cu articolele scanate gresit, nimeni nu sta la finalul cumparaturilor, langa casa de marcaj sa verifice corectitudinea bonului fiscal. Iar daca are ghinionul sa plece din tara in aceeasi zi, trebuie neaparat in 30 zile sa fie inapoi. Sper sa fie cu folos recenzia, chiar cumpar des de la voi.O zi buna !

absa_target: return warranty is negative
translated_Romanian_English: The 1-month term for returning products seems normal and correct to me only for products that the buyer no longer wants due to color, size, or simply doesn't like them. For other reasons, such as incorrect scanning or a defective item, I think the term is too small and should clearly be extended to at least 3-6 months. If someone buys a tent in December, it's clear they won't unpack it until May or June. If they're unlucky and it's defective, it's more complicated to exchange it. It's possible because I've experienced it myself, but maybe it's not always that simple. Also, with incorrectly scanned items, no one stays at the end of their shopping trip near the checkout counter to verify the accuracy of the receipt. And if they have the bad luck to leave the country on the same day, they must return it within 30 days. I hope this review is helpful, as I often buy from you. Have a good day!
translated_English_Chinese: 我认为为期1个月的退货期限对于买家由于颜色、尺寸或简单不喜欢而不想要的产品来说是正常和正确的。然而，对于其他原因，例如扫描错误或商品有缺陷，我认为这个期限太短，应该明确延长至至少3-6个月。如果有人在十二月购买帐篷，很明显他们不会在五月或六月之前拆开它。如果他们不幸遇到缺陷产品，要换货会更加复杂。这种情况是有可能发生的，因为我自己也经历过，但是也许并不总是那么简单。此外，对于扫描错误的商品，没有人会在购物结束时一直呆在收银台附近来核实收据的准确性。如果他们在同一天离开了国家，就必须在30天内退货。希望这篇评论对您有所帮助，因为我经常从你们这里购买。祝你们有美好的一天！
translated_Chinese_Romanian: Consider că o perioadă de returnare a produselor de 1 lună este normală și corectă pentru cumpărători care nu doresc un produs din cauza culorii, dimensiunii sau simplului fapt că nu le place. Cu toate acestea, consider că acest termen este prea scurt pentru alte motive, cum ar fi erori de scanare sau produse defecte, și ar trebui să fie prelungit clar la cel puțin 3-6 luni. Dacă cineva cumpără o cort în decembrie, este evident că nu-l va deschide până în mai sau iunie. Și dacă au ghinionul de a întâlni un produs defect, schimbul va fi și mai complicat. Acest lucru se poate întâmpla, așa cum am experimentat eu însumi, dar perhaps nu este întotdeauna atât de simplu. În plus, pentru produsele cu erori de scanare, nimeni nu va sta lângă casa de marcat pentru a verifica exactitatea chitanței la sfârșitul cumpărăturilor. Și dacă pleacă din țară în aceeași zi, trebuie să returneze produsul în 30 de zile. Sper că această recenzie vă va fi de ajutor, deoarece cumpăr frecvent de la dumneavoastră. Vă urez o zi frumoasă!

translated_Romanian_English: I had ordered a bike online, thus passing for the first time in the Decathlon store. Although I received an email with the order code, it was not found in the store. However, the Decathlon team was very prompt and helped me, and I immediately found the same bike available at the department. I also liked the atmosphere of the store, a relaxing environment, which is why I spent more time in the store, buying some things. My loyalty card was also printed out in a few seconds. I'm very pleased with Decathlon's services, I felt okay, considering that I've worked in sales myself and I know how to read satisfied and capable staff. Congratulations, Decathlon, and thank you for encouraging my passion for sports.
translated_English_Chinese: 我曾在网上订购了一辆自行车，因此第一次走进了迪卡侬商店。虽然我收到了带有订单代码的电子邮件，但商店里却没有找到。然而，迪卡侬团队非常及时地帮助了我，我立即在部门发现了同样的自行车。我也喜欢商店的氛围，一个放松的环境，这就是为什么我在商店里花了更多的时间购买一些东西。我的忠诚卡也被打印出来，只需几秒钟。我对迪卡侬的服务非常满意，我感觉很好，因为我自己曾经从事销售工作，所以我知道如何读懂满意和能干的员工。恭喜迪卡侬，并感谢你们鼓励了我对运动的热情。
translated_Chinese_Romanian: Am comandat o bicicletă online și astfel am ajuns pentru prima dată într-un magazin Decathlon. Deși am primit un e-mail cu codul comenzii, nu am găsit-o în magazin. Echipa Decathlon a fost foarte promptă și mi-a rezolvat problema, iar eu am găsit imediat aceeași bicicletă în secțiune. Mi-a plăcut și atmosfera din magazin, un mediu relaxant, motiv pentru care am stat mai mult și am cumpărat alte lucruri. Cardul meu de fidelitate a fost tipărit în doar câteva secunde. Sunt foarte mulțumit de serviciile Decathlon și m-am simțit bine, pentru că am lucrat și eu în vânzări și știu cum să apreciez angajații competenți și mulțumiți. Felicitări echipei Decathlon și mulțumesc pentru că mi-ați încurajat pasiunea pentru sport.

translated_Romanian_English: I've had this bicycle model since October 2016 and I can say that I'm very satisfied, the bike is very resistant considering I have a weight that oscillates between 125 and 130 kg. During this time, I've used it almost daily to commute to work and occasionally for 30-40 km rides. The only part that 'gave up' after a year and a half of use was the pedal axle, but it seems perfectly normal to me considering my weight and usage frequency, which I replaced on the spot at the Decathlon service. The part was cheap, if I remember correctly, somewhere around 70 lei.
translated_English_Chinese: 我从2016年10月就拥有这辆自行车，到现在我可以说我非常满意，这辆自行车考虑到我的体重在125-130公斤之间，耐用性非常好。在这段时间里，我几乎每天都骑着它去上班，偶尔也会进行30-40公里的骑行。唯一一个在一年半后‘坏掉’的部件是踏板轴，但考虑到我的体重和使用频率，这似乎完全正常。我直接在Decathlon服务中心更换了这个部件。如果我记得正确的话，这个零件很便宜，大约70雷伊。
translated_Chinese_Romanian: Am posedat acest bicicletă din octombrie 2016 și până în prezent pot spune că sunt foarte mulțumit. Având în vedere greutatea mea, care se situează între 125-130 kg, această bicicletă a dovedit o durabilitate excelentă. În acest timp, am folosit-o aproape zilnic pentru a merge la serviciu și, ocazional, am făcut plimbări de 30-40 km. Singurul component care s-a 'stricat' după un an și jumătate a fost axul pedalei, dar având în vedere greutatea mea și frecvența utilizării, acest lucru pare complet normal. Am înlocuit direct această piesă la centrul de service Decathlon. Dacă îmi amintesc corect, piesa a fost foarte ieftină, aproximativ 70 lei.

translated_Romanian_English: I wanted to buy a new bike for my son, the old 20" one was also bought from Decathlon. I went to both Baneasa and Militari stores, albeit on the weekend. There were very few people in the department, busy, I waited 20 minutes for one of them to finish with a customer, and after that, he disappeared. He was also in charge of bike repairs. The staff is what it is, but it's not possible that for a kids' MTB bike 24" you only have one with a steel frame that weighs 15 kg. My son is 30 kg, how can he ride a bike that's half his weight? On your website, you also have more expensive ones with aluminum frames, but they're out of stock in all stores. Luckily, I was able to find something at the Romexpo Bike Salon...
translated_English_Chinese: 我想给儿子买一辆新自行车，旧的20英寸自行车也是在Decathlon买的。我去了巴涅阿萨和米利塔里商店，尽管那是周末。部门里的人很少，很忙，我等了20分钟才有人结束与顾客的对话，但接着他就不见了。他还负责自行车维修。员工就是这样，但是对于一个孩子的24英寸山地自行车，你只有一个钢框架的，重达15公斤。这不可能。我的儿子只有30公斤，他怎么能骑一辆重达他体重一半的自行车呢？在你们的网站上，还有更贵的铝合金框架的，但是所有商店都缺货。幸好，我在罗姆博自行车展上找到了一些东西...
translated_Chinese_Romanian: Vreau să cumpăr un bicicletă nouă pentru fiul meu, vechea bicicletă de 20 de inch a fost cumpărată și ea de la Decathlon. Am mers la magazinele din Băneasa și Militari, chiar dacă era weekend. În departament erau puțini oameni, erau ocupați, am așteptat 20 de minute până când cineva a terminat conversația cu un client, dar apoi a dispărut. El era și responsabil cu reparația bicicletelor. Angajații sunt așa, dar pentru o bicicletă de munte de 24 de inch pentru copii, aveți doar una cu cadru de oțel, care cântărește 15 kilograme. Acest lucru este imposibil. Fiul meu are doar 30 de kilograme, cum ar putea el conduce o bicicletă care cântărește jumătate din greutatea lui? Pe site-ul dvs., există și cadru de aluminiu mai scump, dar toate magazinele sunt în afara stocului. Noroc că am găsit ceva la târgul de biciclete Romexpo...

text: Placa este foarte buna pentru incepatori ca mine. Este super relaxant de folosit ai dupa o ora de utilizare din momentul in care a ajuns am fost cu zambetul pe buze  si garantat o sa mai fiu pentru multa vreme.Livrarea a fost facuta in doua zile lucratoare si a venit invelita in folie cu baloane de aer si iar invelita intr-o folie neagra. Nu avea zgarieturi. +Este super stabila tinand cont ca este prima data cand folosesc o placa indiferent de clasa ei dar fiind prima placa nu stiu prea multe despre concurenta+Este comfortabila si nu prea inalta deci nu am avut probleme cu oboseala picioarelor +este usor de controlat chiar daca kingpin-ul este putin prea strans si la fel si rotile+Nu este nici prea grea nici prea usoara- Lemnul scartie putin la viraje dar este de intensitate mica si poate fi remediat super usor cu putin ulei-rotile sunt putin prea stranse dar iarasi nu este o problema de la producator-Kingpin-ul este putin prea strans astefel virajele sunt cam bruste, asta depinde si de fiecare persoanaDupa prima utilizare pot spune ca o recomand cu incredere celor care vor sa se apuce de longboard-ing sau celor care cauta un mod de relaxare.O sa revin cu informatii dupa o perioada mai mare de uz in caz ca se schimba ceva.

translated_Romanian_English: The board is very good for beginners like me. It's super relaxing to use and after an hour of using it from the moment I got it, I was smiling and guaranteed to be for a long time. The delivery was made in two working days and it came wrapped in plastic with air balloons and again wrapped in a black film. It didn't have any scratches. +It's super stable considering it's the first time I'm using a board, regardless of its class, but being my first board, I don't know much about the competition +It's comfortable and not too high, so I didn't have problems with foot fatigue +it's easy to control even if the kingpin is a bit too tight and also the wheels +It's not too heavy or too light - The wood creaks a little when turning, but it's of low intensity and can be easily fixed with a little oil -The wheels are a bit too tight, but again, it's not a problem from the manufacturer -The kingpin is a bit too tight, so the turns are a bit rough, this also depends on each person. After the first use, I can say that I confidently recommend it to those who want to get into longboarding or those looking for a way to relax. I'll come back with information after a longer period of use in case something changes.
translated_English_Chinese: 这块板对于像我这样的初学者来说非常好。使用它很放松，拿到它后一个小时，我就笑了，保证会用很长时间。货物在两天内送达，装在塑料袋里充满气球，再包上一层黑色薄膜。没有任何划痕。+考虑到这是我第一次使用板，无论其等级如何，但作为我的第一块板，我对竞争对手了解不多+它很舒适，不太高，所以我不会感到脚疲劳+即使王针有点紧，也很容易控制，轮子也一样+它的重量不太重也不太轻-木头在转弯时会发出一点嘎吱声，但强度较低，可以用少量油轻松修复-轮子有点紧，但这不是制造商的问题-王针有点紧，所以转弯会有点粗糙，这也取决于每个人。在第一次使用后，我可以自信地向想要进入长板滑行或寻找放松方式的人推荐它。使用一段时间后，如果有什么变化，我会回来补充信息。
translated_Chinese_Romanian: Această placă este foarte bună pentru începători ca mine. Este relaxant să o folosiți, iar după o oră de la primirea ei, am zâmbit și sunt sigur că o voi folosi mult timp. Marfa a fost livrată în două zile, ambalată într-o pungă de plastic umplută cu aer și acoperită cu o folie neagră subțire. Nu avea nicio urmă de zgârieturi. + Considerând că este prima dată când folosesc o placă, indiferent de nivelul acesteia, dar ca primă placă pentru mine, nu cunosc multe despre concurenți + Este confortabilă, nu prea înaltă, așa că nu mă simt obosit la picioare + Chiar și cu roata reglabilă puțin strânsă, este ușor de controlat, iar roțile sunt la fel + Greutatea sa nu este prea mare sau prea mică - lemnul scoate un sunet slab când se îndoaie, dar acesta poate fi remediat cu o cantitate mică de ulei - roțile sunt puțin strânse, dar acesta nu este o problemă a producătorului - roata reglabilă este puțin strânsă, deci virajele pot fi un pic brutale, dar depinde și de fiecare. După prima utilizare, pot recomanda cu încredere această placă celor care vor să intre în lumea skate-ului sau caută o modalitate de relaxare. Dacă vor apărea schimbări după o perioadă de utilizare, voi reveni cu informații suplimentare.

translated_Romanian_English: I usually do my shopping at Decathlon Berceni. My previous experiences are with Decathlon Spain. Both in Spain and in Berceni, I was never told that we were playing with a ball or that we were playing with anything from the store. On the other hand, the experience in Craiova: the kids (4 & 10 years old) got into a football goal and wanted to kick the ball into it, but I didn't let them because I didn't want to break the goal. Then, a security guard came and told us that it's not allowed because it's on display only, not for playing. Later, while looking for shoes for the little one, the older kid was playing with a ball. A man from the shelves came, looked at him, and signaled him to put the ball down. If we had played a bit more with the football goal, maybe we would have taken it home, according to the kids' words, but it stayed in the store.
translated_English_Chinese: 我通常在Decathlon Berceni購物。我的前幾次經驗是在西班牙的Decathlon。在西班牙和Berceni，我從來沒有被告知我們正在玩球或使用商店裡的東西。另一方面，在克拉約瓦的經驗：孩子們（4歲和10歲）進入了一個足球門，想要把球踢進去，但我不讓他們，因為我不想弄壞門。然後，一名保安過來告訴我們，這是不允許的，因為它只供展示，不準玩。稍後，在給小孩找鞋子的時候，大孩子正在玩一個球。一名從貨架上走過來的人看了他一眼，示意他把球放下。如果我們再玩一會兒足球門，也许我们会把它带回家，根據孩子們的話，但它仍然留在商店里。
translated_Chinese_Romanian: De obicei, cumpăr de la Decathlon Berceni. Primele mele experiențe cu Decathlon au fost în Spania. Atât în Spania, cât și la Berceni, nu mi s-a spus niciodată că nu avem voie să jucăm cu mingile sau cu lucrurile din magazin. Pe de altă parte, experiența mea de la Craiova: copiii (4 și 10 ani) au intrat într-o poartă de fotbal și voiau să împingă mingea, dar nu i-am lăsat pentru că nu voiam să stric poarta. Apoi, un paznic a venit și ne-a spus că nu este permis, pentru că este doar pentru expoziție și nu se poate juca. Mai târziu, când căutam încălțăminte pentru copil, băiatul mai mare se juca cu o minge. Un angajat care trecea pe lângă rafturi l-a privit și i-a făcut semn să lase mingea jos. Dacă am fi jucat puțin mai mult fotbal, poate că am fi putut duce poarta acasă, după cum spuneau copiii, dar a rămas în magazin.

Am vrut sa le cumpar dar pretul aparea de trening adica 75 lei bucata ceea ce este exagerat. Domnisoara mi-a spus sa le cumpar la acel pret sau o sa arunce acei pantaloni deoarece nu poate sa faca reducere de pret.Vreau in continuare sa cumpar cele doua perechi de pantaloni daca le vindeti la un pret rezonabil. Ofer 75 lei pe ambele perechi. Astept un raspuns daca aveti vreo solutie.

translated_Romanian_English: I found in Decathlon Berceni two pairs of 4XL training pants that I needed. It turned out they were from unmatched sets that no longer had jackets. I wanted to buy them, but the price appeared as for a full tracksuit, 75 lei per piece, which is excessive. The lady told me to buy them at that price or she would throw away those pants because she couldn't give me a discount. I still want to buy the two pairs of pants if you sell them at a reasonable price. I offer 75 lei for both pairs. I'm waiting for an answer if you have any solution.
translated_English_Chinese: 我在贝尔切尼的Decathlon发现了两条4XL训练裤，这正是我需要的。结果证明，它们来自不匹配的套装，已经没有外套了。我想买它们，但价格显示为全套运动服，每件75雷伊，這对于我来说是过高的。那位女士告诉我，要么以那个价格购买，要么她就会扔掉那些裤子，因为她不能给我折扣。我仍然想以合理的价格购买这两条裤子，我出价75雷伊買下两条裤子。 我正在等待您的回复，如果您有任何解决方案。
translated_Chinese_Romanian: Am găsit la Decathlon din Berceni două pantaloni de antrenament 4XL, exact ce aveam nevoie. S-a dovedit că provin dintr-un set nelimitat, fără geacă. Vroiam să le cumpăr, dar prețul era afișat pentru întregul set de echipament, 75 de lei per bucată, ceea ce mi se părea prea mult. Doamna mi-a spus că pot să le cumpăr la acel preț sau că le va arunca, deoarece nu poate să-mi ofere o reducere. Totuși, vreau să le cumpăr la un preț rezonabil și am oferit 75 de lei pentru ambele pantaloni. Aștept răspunsul dvs., dacă aveți vreo soluție.

text: Am crezut ca ""livrare la domiciliu"" inseamna livrare la usa. Noroc ca nu am comandat un aparat multifunctional sau produse de o greutate mai mare de 35 de kg. As fi sfarsit prin a le primi in fata blocului, si asta numai in cazul in care curierul ar fi gasit loc de parcare in fata scarii. Altfel as fi primit produsele la coltul strazii cu telefon de instiintare, ce-i drept. Data viitoare criteriul de alegere al magazinului va fi distanta de casa, pentru a ma putea deplasa personal. In cazul asta Decathlonul iese depe lista. In plus, poate firma de curierat se poate concentra pe livrarea integrala a comenzii. Faptul ca aduce un produs o data si isi dau seama ca lipsesc altele din comanda, deci trebuie sa revina, nu ma ajuta. Dimpotriva, imi blocheaza multe ore in care trebuie sa stau acasa sa astept. Pacat de produse, care sunt de o calitate buna.

translated_Romanian_English:
{"translated_text":"I thought that ""home delivery"" meant delivery to the door. Luckily, I didn't order a multi-functional appliance or products weighing more than 35 kg. I would have ended up receiving them in front of the block, and that's only if the courier found parking in front of the stairs. Otherwise, I would have received the products at the corner of the street with a notification call, though. Next time, the criterion for choosing a store will be the distance from my house, so I can go there personally. In this case, Decathlon is out of the list. Additionally, maybe the courier company can focus on delivering the entire order. The fact that they bring one product at a time and then realize that others are missing from the order, so they have to come back, doesn't help me. On the contrary, it blocks many hours when I have to stay home waiting. It's a pity about the products, which are of good quality.",
"language":"English"}
translated_English_Chinese: 我以为“送货上门”是指直接送到家门口。幸好，我没有订购多功能电器或重于35公斤的产品，否则我会在楼块前收到它们，如果快递员能在楼梯前找到停车位的话。否则，我会在街角收到产品，并且还会有通知电话。下次选择商店的标准将是距离我的房子有多远，这样我就可以亲自去那里。在这种情况下，Decathlon已经被排除在名单之外。此外，也许快递公司可以专注于交付整个订单，他们一次只送一个产品，然后意识到其他产品不在订单中，所以他们不得不回来，这对我来说没有任何帮助。相反，它会阻塞很多小时，当我必须呆在家里等待的时候。对于产品质量很好的情况，真是可惜。
translated_Chinese_Romanian: Credeam că „livrarea la ușă” înseamnă direct la intrarea în casă. Din fericire, nu am comandat electrocasnice multifuncționale sau produse care cântăresc mai mult de 35 de kilograme, altfel le-aș fi primit în fața blocului, dacă curierul ar fi găsit un loc de parcare lângă scară. Altfel, aș fi primit produsele la colțul străzii și, în plus, aș fi primit și un apel telefonic de notificare. Data viitoare, criteriul pentru alegerea magazinului va fi distanța față de casa mea, astfel încât să pot merge acolo personal. În acest caz, Decathlon a fost deja exclus din listă. În plus, poate că compania de curierat ar trebui să se concentreze pe livrarea integrală a comenzilor, ei livrează un produs o dată și apoi realizează că alte produse nu fac parte din comandă, așa că trebuie să vină înapoi, ceea ce nu mă ajută deloc. Dimpotrivă, va bloca multe ore, când sunt nevoit să stau acasă și să aștept. Este păcat pentru situațiile în care calitatea produselor este bună.

text: Am comandat o pereche de adidasi pentru ca in magazin nu era disponibila culoarea dorita.Am asteptat 4 zile sa vina o pereche din stocul furnizorului, apoi cand am fost contactat ca au ajuns , am cerut sa mi se schimbe adresa de livrare(operatie confirmata de operatorul telefonic).Dupa alte 2 zile am fost sunat de curier la vechea adresa ,si nu am putut prelua pentru ca fan courier nu poate livra produsul dupa ora 16.Am sunat la Decathlon si un alt operator a schimbat din nou adresa de livrare si dupa inca o zi , adidasii au ajuns unde trebuiau.Marimea este ok, calitatea la fel.

translated_Romanian_English: I ordered a pair of sneakers because the desired color was not available in the store. I waited 4 days for a pair to arrive from the supplier's stock, and then when I was contacted that they had arrived, I asked for my delivery address to be changed (operation confirmed by the telephone operator). After another 2 days, I was called by the courier at the old address, and I couldn't pick up because the courier can't deliver the product after 4 pm. I called Decathlon and another operator changed the delivery address again, and after one more day, the sneakers arrived where they were supposed to. The size is okay, the quality is the same.
translated_English_Chinese: 我订购了一双运动鞋，因为商店里没有想要的颜色。我等了4天，供应商的库存才到货，当我被通知有货时，我要求将我的送货地址更改（电话操作员确认了此操作）。又过了2天，快递员在旧址联系了我，但我无法取货，因为快递员不能在下午4点后送货。我打电话给Decathlon，另一个操作员再次更改了送货地址，经过一天后，运动鞋到达了它应该去的地方。尺寸没问题，质量也是一样的。
translated_Chinese_Romanian: Am comandat o pereche de pantofi de sport, pentru că magazinul nu avea culoarea dorită. Am așteptat 4 zile până când stocul furnizorului a sosit, iar când am fost anunțat că este disponibil, am solicitat schimbarea adresei mele de livrare (operatorul de telefon a confirmat această operațiune). După încă două zile, curierul m-a contactat la vechea adresă, dar nu am putut prelua coletul, deoarece curierul nu putea livra după ora 16.00. Am sunat la Decathlon, un alt operator a schimbat din nou adresa de livrare și, după o zi, pantofii de sport au ajuns unde trebuiau. Dimensiunea a fost corectă, iar calitatea a fost la fel.

text: Am comandat 2 porti de fotbal, in data de 10.04.2018, care ar fi trebuit in data de 12, cel tarziu 13 sa fie in magazin, dar nu s-a intamplat asa! Am dezamagit un copil de 7 ani, deoarece erau cadou de ziua de nastere!

translated_Romanian_English: I ordered 2 football gates on 10.04.2018, which were supposed to be in the store by the 12th, at the latest by the 13th, but it didn't happen! I disappointed a 7-year-old child because they were a birthday gift!
translated_English_Chinese: 我在2018年4月10日订购了2个足球门，应该在12日之前到货，最晚也应在13日到货，但没有！我让一个7岁的孩子失望，因为这是他的生日礼物！
translated_Chinese_Romanian: Am comandat pe 10 aprilie 2018 două porți de fotbal, care ar fi trebuit să sosească înainte de data de 12, iar cel târziu ar fi trebuit să sosească pe 13, dar nu a fost așa! Am dezamăgit un copil de 7 ani, deoarece aceasta era cadoul lui de ziua de naștere!

text: Foarte de treaba baietii de la atelier dar nu au fost in stare sa-mi regleze deraiorul pe fata de la o bicicleta BTWIN Triban 500 noua. A trebuit sa ma intorc de vreo 6 ori cu ea la reglat,  si sa platesc pentru o reglare deficitara desi bicicleta nu avea mai mult de o luna. In final am ales sa ma duc la un atelier de cartier unde mi-au facut-o cum trebuie din prima incercare.  Cineva ar trebui ori sa ii invete sa regleze corect bicletele vandute de propriul magazin ori ar trebui sa angajati mai multi oameni la atelier pentru ca nu i-am vazut sa stea o secunda locului. Daca sunt suprasolicitati, mi se pare normal sa faca greseli.. Multumesc.

translated_Romanian_English: The guys at the workshop were very nice but they couldn't manage to adjust the derailleur on my new BTWIN Triban 500 bike. I had to return about 6 times for adjustments and pay for a deficient adjustment even though the bike was less than a month old. In the end, I chose to go to a local workshop where they did it correctly from the first try. Someone should either teach them how to adjust the bikes sold by their own store or hire more people at the workshop because I didn't see them standing still for a second. If they're overworked, I think it's normal that they make mistakes.. Thank you.
translated_English_Chinese: 车间的伙计们很友好，但他们无法调整我的新BTWIN Triban 500自行车的变速器。我不得不返回大约6次进行调整，并且为缺陷的调整付费，尽管自行车不到一个月大。最终，我选择去当地的一个车间，他们第一次就做对了。有人应该教他们如何调整他们自己商店销售的自行车，或者在车间雇佣更多的人，因为我没有看到他们有一刻停下来的时间。如果他们工作过度，我认为他们会犯错是正常的。谢谢。
translated_Chinese_Romanian: Băieții de la atelier erau foarte prietenoși, dar nu au putut regla schimbătorul de viteze al noului meu bicicletă BTWIN Triban 500. Trebuia să mă întorc de aproximativ 6 ori pentru a face ajustările și am plătit pentru ajustarea defectului, deși bicicleta avea mai puțin de o lună. În cele din urmă, am ales să merg la un atelier local și ei au făcut totul corect de la început. Cineva ar trebui să-i învețe cum să regleze bicicletele pe care le vând în magazinul lor sau să angajeze mai mult personal, pentru că nu i-am văzut o clipă fără să fie ocupați. Dacă sunt suprasolicitați, consider că este normal să facă greșeli. Mulțumesc.

Nu aveti nimic de pierdut ci numai de castigat... </s>
absa_target: price is negative; shop organization is negative; staff competency is negative
translated_Romanian_English: A hand flexor exposed without price on the shelf. Being interested in it, I asked the staff who found out from behind the scenes a price that was at least exaggerated, and also incomplete. I was disappointed by the communicated price (obviously an exaggeration), because I would have liked to buy it even incomplete... I recommend flexibility in such situations... You have nothing to lose but everything to gain...
translated_English_Chinese: 货架上有一只手指弯曲的产品，没有标价。对此很感兴趣，我向工作人员询问，他们从后台查出来的价格不仅夸张，而且还不完整。我对告知我的价格感到失望（显然是夸大了），因为我原本想买下它，即使是不完整的... 在这种情况下，我建议灵活处理... 你没有什么可失去的，但可以获得一切...
translated_Chinese_Romanian: Pe raft exista un produs cu degetul curbat, fara pret. Am fost foarte interesat si l-am intrebat pe angajat, dar pretul pe care l-au gasesit in spate a fost nu numai exagerat, ci si incomplet. Am fost dezamagit de pretul care mi-a fost comunicat (era evident ca a fost exagerat), pentru ca initial voiam sa il cumpar, chiar daca era incomplet... In aceasta situatie, sugerez sa procedam flexibil... Nu aveti nimic de pierdut, dar puteti castiga totul...

text: Buna ziua,Doresc sa va aduc la cunostinta urmatoarea intamplare:Sambata 07.05.2016 am cumparat din magazinul Baneasa 2 trotinete: una town 7xl si una town 5EF.Am iesit cu ele in parc in aceeasi zi. Town 5EF are un sistem inovativ de pliere dar care nu a functionat.In aceeasi zi m-am intors cu ea si seful de raion a fost foarte amabil, dupa ce a verificat problema si a constatat ca trotineta nu se mai putea plia (nu functiona butonul), mi-a inlocuit-o.Duminica dimineata cand sa plec cu cea noua am constatat ca avea directia intepenita (era infranat ghidonul stanga-dreapta). M-am intors si cu asta la magazinul din Baneasa dar acum am avut parte de-o cu totul alta atitudine din partea sefului de raion care era altul: vroia s-o dea la service s-o ""repare"". Am refuzat acest lucru dat fiind ca era un produs nou, neutilizat si mi se parea normal sa fie inlocuit atata timp cat nici nu s-a facut vreo proba la achizitie.Nervos pe toata perioada discutiei m-a plimbat cu tot felul de ""argumente"", ca ele mai trebuiesc reglate, ca mai ies asa din productie, ca d-aia sunt acolo...etcMi s-a parut anormal ca un produs nou sa nu fie perfect functional la cumparare unde si pretul nu era deloc mic pentru o trotinetata, 479,9 lei.L-am rugat sa-mi spuna cum se numeste dar se facea ca nu aude, noroc c-avea un ecuson si (parca) Dragos era numele lui.Mi-a inlocuit-o pana la urma, cea primita functionand ireprosabil azi, dupa o tura prin Herastrau :).

translated_Romanian_English: Good day, I want to bring to your attention the following incident: On Saturday, 07.05.2016, I bought from Baneasa 2 store two scooters: one Town 7xl and one Town 5EF. I took them out to the park on the same day. The Town 5EF has an innovative folding system but it didn't work. On the same day, I returned with it and the department manager was very kind, after checking the problem and finding that the scooter could no longer be folded (the button didn't work), he replaced it. On Sunday morning when I wanted to leave with the new one, I found out that it had a stuck direction (the left-right handlebar was jammed). I returned with it to the Baneasa store but now I had a completely different attitude from the department manager who was another person: he wanted to send it to service to "repair" it. I refused this because it was a new, unused product and it seemed normal to me that it should be replaced as long as no testing was done at purchase. Nervous throughout the discussion, he walked me through all sorts of "arguments", like they need to be adjusted, they come out like that from production, that's why they're there... etc. It seemed abnormal to me that a new product shouldn't be perfectly functional at purchase, especially since the price wasn't small for a scooter, 479.9 lei. I asked him to tell me his name but he pretended not to hear, luckily he had a badge and (I think) his name was Dragos. He replaced it in the end, the one I received working flawlessly today, after a ride through Herastrau :).
translated_English_Chinese: 你好，我想将以下事件引起您的注意：2016年05月07日星期六，我从巴内萨2号店购买了两辆滑板车：一辆Town 7xl和一辆Town 5EF。我当天就把它们拿到公园里。 Town 5EF有一个创新的折叠系统，但它不能用。当天我就带着它回去，部门经理非常友好，在检查了问题并发现滑板车不能再折叠（按钮不工作）后，他替换了它。星期日早晨，当我想离开时，我发现新买的滑板车方向卡住了（左-right把手被卡住）。我带着它回到巴内萨商店，但现在部门经理的态度完全不同：他想送去维修。但是我拒绝了，因为这是一个新的、未使用过的产品，似乎正常的是应该替换掉，而不是进行维修。在讨论过程中，他变得很紧张，并给我讲述各种“理由”，比如它们需要调整，它们是这样从生产线出来的，这就是为什么他们存在...等等。对我来说，一个新的产品不应该在购买时完美地发挥作用似乎是不正常的，尤其是价格不是很小，为479.9雷伊。我要求他告诉我他的名字，但他装作没听见，幸运的是，他有一个徽章，我想他的名字叫Dragos。最后，他还是替换了它，我今天骑着新滑板车进行了一次Herastrau之旅，没有任何问题：）
translated_Chinese_Romanian: Bună ziua, aș vrea să aduc în atenția dumneavoastră următorul eveniment: sâmbătă, 07.05.2016, am cumpărat de la magazinul Baneasa 2 două skateboard-uri: un Town 7xl și un Town 5EF. Le-am dus în aceeași zi la parc. Town 5EF are un sistem de pliere inovativ, dar nu funcționa. L-am returnat în aceeași zi, iar managerul de departament a fost foarte amabil, a verificat problema și, după ce a constatat că skateboard-ul nu se mai putea plia (butonul nu funcționa), mi l-a înlocuit. Duminică dimineață, când am vrut să plec, am descoperit că noua mea skateboard are direcția blocată (mânerul stânga-dreapta era blocat). L-am dus înapoi la magazinul Baneasa, dar acum managerul de departament a avut o atitudine complet diferită: voia să îl trimită în service. Dar eu am refuzat, pentru că este un produs nou și neutilizat și mi se pare normal ca acesta să fie înlocuit, nu reparat. În timpul discuției, el a devenit foarte agitat și mi-a spus diverse „motivații”, cum ar fi că trebuie reglate, că ies așa de pe linia de producție, că asta e normal... etc. Pentru mine, un produs nou nu ar trebui să funcționeze perfect la cumpărare pare anormal, mai ales că prețul nu este mic, 479,9 lei. I-am cerut să-mi spună numele, dar el a făcut pe surdul, noroc cu insigna lui, cred că îl cheamă Dragos. În final, el m-a înlocuit și astăzi am făcut o plimbare cu noua mea skateboard la Herastrau, fără niciun fel de probleme: )

Întrebările și solicitările mele au fost legate de verificarea punctelor acumulate, modul în care pot verifica singur aceste puncte, verificarea adresei de e-mail corectă, deoarece anul acesta nu am primit niciun e-mail. Îmi plac produsele Decathlon, iar în fiecare sezon cumpărăm pentru întreaga familie. Aș dori ca personalul magazinului și operatorii să fie prietenoși, și, dacă este posibil, chiar zâmbitori, ar fi foarte bine. Găsirea unor produse diverse și de calitate la prețuri rezonabile. Uneori, în magazinele din Ploiești, găsesc lucruri care mă bucură.

I called Bucharest and found out that the delivery had been made. In the end, a completely different model of helmet arrived than the one I wanted...

translated_Chinese_Romanian: Am comandat un căști de schi de la Decathlon din Timișoara și am lăsat numărul meu de telefon pentru a fi contactat atunci când căștile sosesc. Am sunat la București și abia atunci am aflat că marfa a sosit. Și, în final, căștile care au venit erau complet diferite de ceea ce voi comandat…

text: Am cumparat o banda de alergare Proform S7. Este dezamagitoare , scartaie din toate incheieturile. La cat costa si la cat de recomandata este, plus ca au pus pe pe ea si "" cel mai bine  vandut produs"" ...este un maxim de dezamagire. translated_English_Chinese: 我买了一个普罗夫曼S7跑步机。它令人失望，所有的关节都发出吱嘎声。考虑到它的价格和推荐程度，以及他们在上面贴上了“畅销产品”的标签......这是一个最大程度上的失望。这台跑步机非常重，根据规格重达92公斤，两个人无法将其抬起，因为重量没有平衡。客服人员告诉我们自己把它带回商店.....哇！如果冰箱的人也这样对我，我们都将会残疾。他们没有送货上门的服务，即使收费也不愿意来，说我们只能自己给它加油，如果不拿回来的话。对于一款3000莱元的产品，这是一个很好的建议。我后悔没有在线购买，这样他们就会被迫在不发表评论的情况下取回它。

Ei nu au serviciu de livrare, chiar și contra cost, și ne-au spus că trebuie să-i punem uleiul noi înșine, dacă nu-l luăm înapoi. Pentru un produs de 3000 lei, este o sugestie bună. Regret că nu l-am cumpărat online, așa ar fi trebuit să-l ia înapoi fără să poată face comentarii.

translated_Romanian_English: There is a varied range of products, so you can reorient yourself if needed. translated_Chinese_Romanian: Aici există multe produse, astfel încât puteți ajusta direcția după cum este necesar. În timpul plății, operatorul Decathlon, în afară de clientul din fața lui, se ocupă și de multe alte lucruri - apeluri telefonice de la colegi, discuții cu securitatea, discuții cu clienții etc. Așteptarea este neplăcută.

text: De cate ori vin in magazin, mai ales in weekend, e o atmosfera extrem de incarcata...foarte multi parinti vin cu copiii aici sa se joace in incinta magazinului. E foarte multa galagie, trebuie sa te feresti de copiii cu biciclete, trotinete mingi etc...chiar am fost lovita de un copil cu o bicicleta, copilul nu era supravegheat ...nu am facut scandal, deoarece stiu ca nu a fost cu intentie. Dar: in primul rand, am o operatie la genunchiul drept de implant de ligamente, dupa un accident grav la ski...si inca nu sunt refacuta complet( daca eram lovita mai rau si va dadeam in judecata , credeti ca era ok ? ) In al doilea rand: este magazin , nu loc de joaca . Inteleg sa testeze produsele, dar , in acest magazin, in fiecare wekend este o harababura totala. Sub aparenta testarii produselor, de fapt, isi aduc copiii sa se joace ca la un loc de joaca. Si, cel mai periculos, majoritatea copiilor sunt nesupravegheati, parintii fiind ocupati cu altele... In Decathlonul din Budapesta nu se intampla asa ceva !

absa_target: environment is negative
translated_Romanian_English: Every time I come to the store, especially on weekends, there's an extremely crowded atmosphere...many parents bring their children here to play inside the store. It's very noisy, you have to watch out for kids with bicycles, scooters, balls, etc...I was even hit by a child with a bike, the child was not supervised...I didn't make a scene because I know it wasn't on purpose. But: first of all, I have a knee operation for ligament implant after a serious skiing accident...and I'm still not fully recovered (if I were hit worse and took you to court, would that be okay?). Secondly: this is a store, not a playground. I understand testing products, but in this store, every weekend is total chaos. Under the guise of testing products, they actually bring their kids to play like it's a playground. And the most dangerous thing is that most children are unsupervised, with parents busy doing other things...In Decathlon Budapest, such things don't happen!
translated_English_Chinese: 每次我来到商店，特别是在周末，总是非常拥挤……很多家长带着孩子来商店里玩。这里很吵闹，你必须注意有孩子骑自行车、滑板车、球等的安全。我甚至被一个骑自行车的孩子撞到了，那个孩子没有人看管……我没有大声喧哗，因为我知道那不是故意的。但是：首先，我刚做了膝盖手术，植入韧带，是因为之前滑雪事故严重受伤……而且我还没完全恢复（如果我被撞得更严重，然后把你告上法庭，那会不会行？）。其次：这是商店，不是游乐场。我理解测试产品，但是这个商店，每个周末都是一片混乱。他们以测试产品为借口，实际上却把孩子带来像在游乐场一样玩。而且最危险的是，大多数孩子都是无人看管的，父母忙着做其他事情……在布达佩斯的Decathlon，这种事情是不会发生的！
translated_Chinese_Romanian: De fiecare dată când vin la magazin, în special în week-end, este foarte aglomerat... mulți părinți aduc copiii lor să se joace în magazin. În al doilea rând: acesta este un magazin, nu o zonă de joacă. Înțeleg testarea produselor, dar în acest magazin, fiecare week-end este haos. Și cel mai periculos lucru este că majoritatea copiilor sunt nesupravegheați, părinții fiind ocupați cu alte lucruri... În Decathlon din Budapesta, astfel de lucruri nu se întâmplă!

text: Sambata, 24 octombrie. Am probat toate marcile si modelele de clapari disponibile. M-am oprit la Rossignol Alltrack 90. Din pacate, pretul de la raft (699,90) era peste bugetul disponibil in acel moment. O angajata de pe raion mi-a spus ca e posibil ca pretul sa fie redus, si mi-a facut si o calculatie, ajungand cu oferta de pret la 611 lei. O reducere consistenta si semnificativa! Din pacate, inca prea mult pentru cati bani aveam la mine in acel moment, si pentru bugetul gandit initial pentru aceasta achizitie. A ramas sa ma gandesc si sa anunt daca vreau sa mi-i rezerve.Luni, 26 octombrie.M-am decis sa aloc cei 611 lei pentru achizitionarea claparilor. Intre timp am facut rost si de bani! Am sunat la magazin sa-i rezerv, iar aceeasi angajata cu care am discutat cu 2 zile inainte mi-a spus ca seful de magazin nu e de acord cu reducerea, ca pretul e si-asa redus si ca, daca vreau sa-i cumpar, ii pot cumpara doar cu pretul de raft, adica 699,90. Am intrebat-o pe angajata Decathlon ce s-ar fi intamplat daca totusi as fi cumparat sambata claparii, la pretul propus si redus, de 611 lei, si mi-a spus ca nu stie ce s-ar fi intamplat in aceasta situatie.Uitandu-ma pe situl Decathlon, am constatat cu surprindere ca pretul de site e intr-adevar mai mare cu 100 de lei (799,90) decat pretul de la raft. Am rezervat  telefonic marfa si in 2 ore am fost in magazin si am cumparat-o, la pretul de raft. Poate ar fi trebuit sa nu mai calc in Decathlon, dar sunt un om pragmatic, si ACEI clapari imi veneau perfect. Asa ca, i-am cumparat.Incerc sa ""inghit"" si sa accept situatia, dar am ramas totusi cu dezamagirea ca mi s-a ""fluturat"" pe la nas o oferta, care ulterior mi-a fost retrasa. Asa ceva nu se face!Recomand in continuare acest magazin, cu rezerva ca, atunci cand vi se face o oferta, sa profitati imediat de ea...

Unfortunately, still too much for how much money I had with me at that moment, and for the initial budget planned for this purchase. It remained for me to think about it and announce if I want to reserve them. Monday, October 26. I decided to allocate the 611 lei for the ski purchase. In the meantime, I also got some more money! I called the store to reserve them, and the same employee with whom I discussed two days earlier told me that the store manager does not agree with the reduction, that the price is already reduced, and if I want to buy them, I can only do so at the shelf price, which is 699.90. I asked the Decathlon employee what would have happened if I had bought the skis on Saturday at the proposed and reduced price of 611 lei, and she told me that she doesn't know what would have happened in that situation. Looking on the Decathlon website, I was surprised to find that the website price is indeed 100 lei (799.90) more than the shelf price. translated_English_Chinese: 10月24日星期六。我试过所有品牌和型号的滑雪板，最终停留在Rossignol Alltrack 90上。不幸的是，货架价格（699.90）超过了当时可用的预算。来自该部门的一名员工告诉我，价格可能会降低，她甚至进行了计算，达到了611莱伊的报价。一个显著的折扣！不幸的是，对于我当时带着的钱和最初计划用于此次购买的预算来说仍然太多，只能让我思考一下是否要预订它们。10月26日星期一，我决定为滑雪板购买分配611莱伊。同时，我也获得了一些更多的钱！我打电话给商店进行预订，两天前与我讨论的同一名员工告诉我，店长不同意降价，价格已经降低，如果我想买它们，只能以货架价格699.90购买。我问Decathlon员工，如果我在星期六以611莱伊的降价购买滑雪板会发生什么，她说她不知道如果那样的话会发生什么情况。在Decathlon网站上，我惊讶地发现网站上的价格确实比货架价格高出100莱伊（799.90）。我通过电话预订了商品，两个小时内，我来到了商店，以货架价格购买了它们。也许我不应该回到Decathlon，但我是一个务实的人，那些滑雪板非常适合我，所以我买下了它们。我试图接受和接受这种情况，但我仍然对提出了然后从我这里撤回的报价感到失望。这不是做事的方式！我仍然推荐这家商店，需要注意的是，当你被提供一个报价时，要立即利用它……
translated_Chinese_Romanian: Pe 24 octombrie, sâmbătă, am încercat toate mărcile și modelele de snowboard și, în final, m-am oprit la Rossignol Alltrack 90. Din nefericire, prețul de raft (699,90) a depășit bugetul disponibil pe atunci. Un angajat din departament mi-a spus că prețul ar putea fi redus și chiar a făcut niște calcule, ajungând la o ofertă de 611 lei. O reducere semnificativă! Din nefericire, era încă prea mult pentru banii pe care îi aveam asupra mea atunci și pentru bugetul initial planificat pentru această achiziție, astfel că m-am gândit dacă ar trebui să le rezerv. Pe 26 octombrie, luni, am decis să aloc 611 lei pentru snowboarduri. De asemenea, am obținut și niște bani în plus! Am sunat la magazin pentru a rezerva produsele și același angajat cu care discutasem cu două zile în urmă mi-a spus că șeful departamentului nu a fost de acord cu reducerea prețului, iar dacă vreau să le cumpăr, va trebui să plătesc prețul de raft de 699,90. L-am întrebat pe angajatul Decathlon ce s-ar fi întâmplat dacă aș fi cumpărat snowboardurile sâmbătă la prețul redus de 611 lei și mi-a spus că nu știe ce s-ar fi întâmplat în acest caz. Pe site-ul Decathlon, am descoperit cu surprindere că prețul de pe site este cu 100 lei mai mare decât prețul de raft (799,90). Am făcut o comandă telefonică și, în două ore, am ajuns la magazin și le-am cumpărat la prețul de raft. Poate că nu ar fi trebuit să mă întorc la Decathlon, dar sunt un om practic și acele snowboarduri îmi plăceau foarte mult, așa că le-am cumpărat. Încerc să accept și să înțeleg situația, dar încă mai sunt dezamagit de faptul că mi-a fost oferit un preț și apoi retras. Acesta nu este modul în care ar trebui să se facă lucrurile! Încă recomand acest magazin, dar trebuie să aveți grijă când vi se oferă un preț...

translated_Romanian_English: At the bicycle department, I went to two different stores to find an XL-sized bike. Meanwhile, in other departments, others were just browsing merchandise while their colleague from the bicycle department was overwhelmed. The line behind me had over 5 people - so some people waited more than 30 minutes.
translated_English_Chinese: 在自行车部门，我去两个不同的商店找了一辆超大号的自行车。当我找到想要的东西时，我等了30分钟，想跟你们的一个技工讨论一下，他一个人值班（他告诉我他的同事不负责任，已经辞职了）。与此同时，在其他部门，别人只是浏览商品，而他们来自自行车部门的同事却被压得喘不过气来。在我身后排队的人有5个以上，所以有些人等待了超过30分钟。
translated_Chinese_Romanian: În departamentul de biciclete, am mers în două magazine diferite pentru a găsi o bicicletă de dimensiuni foarte mari. Când am găsit ceea ce căutam, am așteptat 30 de minute pentru a discuta cu unul dintre mecanicii dvs., care era singur la schimb (mi-a spus că colegul său era neglijent și a demisionat). Între timp, în alte departamente, oamenii se uitau doar la produse, în timp ce colegii lor din departamentul de biciclete erau copleșiți. În spatele meu, în fila de așteptare, erau peste cinci persoane, astfel încât unii oameni au așteptat mai mult de 30 de minute.

text: Sunt un client fidel Decathlon si imi place sa vizitez magazinul in mod regulat. L-am recomandat multor prieteni si probabil ca o voi face in continuare pentru produsele unice, de foarte buna calitate iar atmosfera foarte prietenoasa.In magazinul din Baneasa am avut primele experiente oarecum neplacute. Produsele mi s-au parut dezorganizate la raft si a trebuit sa caut foarte mult ceea ce doream sa cumpar si sa cer ajutorul angajatilor (foarte amabili dealtfel). Acelasi produs era expus in mai multe locuri iar articolele din aceeasi game mi s-au parut expuse pe rafturi diferite. Poate ca este vorba de un magazin nou cu care nu m-am obisnuit inca.Aspectul mai neplacut a fost la plata de la casa cand sistemul de incasare wireless a facut exact opusul a ce ar trebui sa faca, a ingreunat foarte mutl inregistrarea produselor. A trebuit sa ne departam cu cosul de cumparaturi de casa pentru ca acesta sa nu inregistreze produsele de mai multe ori (asa mi s-a spus). Apoi sa luam produs cu produs, sa le inmanam casierului care sa le treaca prin fata aparatului de multiple ori pana la marcare. La final mi se spune ca este posibil sa nu fi marcat ceva, Dupa care trebuie sa luam produsele unul cate unul si sa incercam sa le idenficam pe displayul casei de marcat... intregul proces a durat cam 10-15 minute, in conditiile in care am achizitionat aproximativ 10 produse. O experienta placuta la cumparaturi e incununanta cu o experienta agasanta la casa de marcat. Este pacat. Sunt convins ca sistemul se va imbunatati. Ca si nota de final voi ramane in continuare un client multumit Decathlon si sper doar ca informatiile de mai sus vor fi folosite pentru imbunanatirea serviciilor, nu percepute ca o reclamatie furioasa.
aspects_polarities: {'choices': ['environment - positive', 'product - positive', 'quality - positive', 'shop organization - negative', 'staff competency - positive', 'service - negative']}

translated_Romanian_English: I'm a loyal Decathlon customer and I like to visit the store regularly. I've recommended it to many friends and will probably continue to do so because of the unique, high-quality products and the very friendly atmosphere. In the Baneasa store, I had some unpleasant experiences at first. The products seemed disorganized on the shelves and I had to search a lot for what I wanted to buy and ask the employees (who were very kind, by the way) for help. The same product was displayed in multiple places and items from the same range seemed to be displayed on different shelves. Maybe it's just a new store that I'm not used to yet. The more unpleasant aspect was at the checkout when the wireless payment system did exactly the opposite of what it should have done, making it very difficult to register the products. We had to move away from the checkout with our shopping cart so that it wouldn't register the products multiple times (that's what I was told). Then we had to take each product one by one and hand them to the cashier to scan them multiple times until they were marked. In the end, I was told that it's possible that some items might not have been registered, after which we had to take the products one by one and try to identify them on the checkout display... the whole process took about 10-15 minutes, considering I bought around 10 products. A pleasant shopping experience is ruined by an annoying experience at the checkout. It's a shame. I'm convinced that the system will improve. As a final note, I will remain a satisfied Decathlon customer and I hope that the above information will be used to improve the services, not perceived as an angry complaint.
translated_English_Chinese: 我是一个忠实的Decathlon顾客，我喜欢定期去商店。由于独特的高质量产品和非常友好的氛围，我已经向很多朋友推荐了它，并且可能会继续这样做。在Baneasa商店，我最初有一些不愉快的经历。货架上的商品似乎很混乱，我不得不花费很多时间寻找我想要购买的东西，并向员工（顺便说，他们非常友好）寻求帮助。同一个产品在多个地方都有展示，而同一系列的物品似乎被展示在不同的货架上。也许这只是我还不习惯的一个新商店。在结账时，更加令人恼火的是无线支付系统做了相反的事情，使得注册商品变得非常困难。我们不得不离开收银台带着我们的购物车，以免重复注册商品（就像我被告知的那样）。然后，我们不得不一件一件地取出每个产品，并把它们递给收银员多次扫描，直到它们被标记。在最后，我被告知，有些物品可能没有被注册，于是我们不得不再次一件一件地取出这些商品，并试图在结账显示屏上识别它们……整个过程花了大约10-15分钟，考虑到我购买了大约10个产品。愉快的购物体验被收银台令人烦恼的经历所破坏。真可惜。我相信这个系统会改进。最后，我仍然是一个满意的Decathlon顾客，我希望上述信息能够用于改善服务，而不是被视为愤怒的投诉。
translated_Chinese_Romanian: Sunt un client fidel al Decathlon și îmi place să merg regulat în magazine. Din cauza produselor de calitate superioară și a atmosferei extrem de prietenoase, am recomandat-o deja multor prieteni și probabil voi continua să o fac. La magazinul din Băneasa, inițial am avut câteva experiențe neplăcute. Produsele de pe rafturi păreau a fi în dezordine, trebuia să petrec mult timp căutând ceea ce voiam să cumpăr și să cer ajutorul angajaților (care, între timp, au fost foarte prietenoși). Același produs era expus în mai multe locuri, iar articolele din aceeași serie păreau a fi expuse pe rafturi diferite. Poate că acesta este doar un magazin nou cu care nu sunt încă obișnuit. La casă, mai frustrant a fost faptul că sistemul de plată wireless a făcut contrariul, făcând foarte dificilă înregistrarea produselor. Trebuia să părăsim casa de marcat cu căruciorul nostru de cumpărături pentru a evita înregistrarea repetată a produselor (așa cum mi s-a spus). Apoi, trebuia să scoatem produsele una câte una și să le dăm casierului de mai multe ori pentru a le scana până ce au fost marcate. La final, mi s-a spus că unele articole nu ar fi putut fi înregistrate, astfel încât trebuia să scoatem produsele una câte una și să încercăm să le identificăm pe ecranul de la casă... Întregul proces a durat aproximativ 10-15 minute, având în vedere că am cumpărat aproximativ 10 produse. Experiența plăcută de cumpărături a fost distrusă de experiența frustrantă de la casă. Păcat. Sper ca acest sistem să se îmbunătățească. În final, rămân un client mulțumit al Decathlon și sper că informațiile de mai sus vor fi folosite pentru a îmbunătăți serviciul, și nu vor fi privite ca o plângere furioasă.

translated_Romanian_English: Good day. I bought this bike about 8 months ago and I've had nothing but problems with it. After less than 2 months, the rear tire exploded, maximum wear on the outer tire, not covered by warranty because they said I braked excessively, okay I paid. After another 3-4 months, the tire needs to be changed again, very poor quality, I don't recommend Decathlon tires. Then, while riding, the rear pinion that changes gears broke, to my surprise this was replaced under warranty, but the repair person told me it's still my fault because I didn't grease the chain, I don't understand what this has to do with the chain since it broke while I was changing gears. In conclusion, I regret buying this bike and I don't recommend it.
translated_English_Chinese: 你好，我大约8个月前买了这辆自行车，从那时起我就一直遇到问题。在不到2个月的时间里，后胎爆炸了，外胎磨损最大，不在保修范围内，因为他们说我过度刹车，好吧，我付了钱。又过了3-4个月，轮胎需要再次更换，质量很差，我不推荐迪卡侬轮胎。然后，当我骑行时，变速的后齿轮断了，令我惊讶的是，这是在保修期内被替换的，但是维修人员告诉我，这仍然是我的错，因为我没有给链条上油，我不明白这与链条有什么关系，因为它在我换档时断了。总之，我后悔买了这辆自行车，并不推荐它。
translated_Chinese_Romanian: Salut, am cumpărat bicicleta aceasta cu aproximativ 8 luni în urmă și de atunci am întâmpinat mereu probleme. În mai puțin de 2 luni, anvelopa din spate a explodat, iar cea externă s-a uzat excesiv, nefiind acoperită de garanție, pentru că ei au spus că am frânat prea tare, bine, am plătit. Apoi, după alți 3-4 luni, a trebuit să înlocuiesc din nou anvelopa, calitatea fiind foarte slabă, nu recomand anvelopele Decathlon. În plus, când conduceam, roata din spate cu schimbător de viteze s-a rupt, ceea ce m-a surprins, a fost înlocuită în garanție, dar mecanicul mi-a spus că tot este vina mea, pentru că nu am uns lanțul, nu înțeleg ce are a face lanțul cu asta, deoarece s-a rupt când schimbam viteza. În orice caz, regret cumpărarea acestei biciclete și nu o recomand.

translated_Chinese_Romanian: Noua modalitate de plată este foarte dezamăgitoare, am așteptat jumătate de oră la primul casier, în timp ce alți clienți mai îndrăzneți au mers direct la alte case goale pentru a plăti, dar ne-au refuzat și ne-au spus că ar trebui să așteptăm la primul casier. În general, a fost haos! La primul casier coada era cea mai lungă, merită un premiu pentru că a procesat cele mai multe tranzacții și a trebuit să ofere informații clienților, deoarece nu existau instrucțiuni sau indicații care să explice cum să urmăm noile reguli.

absa_input: Atrageti oamenii cu oferte speciale si preturi mici pe care nu le aveti pe stoc !!! Ar trebui ca stocurile de marfa sa fie refacute in functie de vanzari si nu de alte criterii. Astfel ar fi disponibile mereu si numerele mari la incaltamintea barbateasca la oferta. E normal sa suplimentezi mai mult stocurile care se vand mai mult pentru ca fiecare reper sa fie disponibil permanent clientilor. Daca ai observat ca numerele mari se dau imediat si cele mici zac luni de zile pe stoc, nu e logic ca data viitoare vei baga pe stoc mult mai multe numere mari decat cele mici? La voi nu e logic se pare... Ultima data am cheltuit aproape 1000 lei pe carpe si vroiam 4~5 perechi de mergatori pentru mine si angajatii mei ca incaltaminte de munca. Nu ma gasit nimik pe numere mari ! Merci pentru nimic si voi cumpara din alte magazine si voi vizita mai rar pe al dvs.. </s>
absa_target: shop diversity is negative; promotions is negative
translated_Romanian_English: Attract people with special offers and low prices that you don't even have in stock!!! The merchandise stocks should be refilled based on sales, not other criteria. This way, large sizes of men's shoes would always be available at the offer. It's normal to supplement the stocks that sell more so that each item is permanently available to customers. If you've noticed that large sizes are sold immediately and small ones stay in stock for months, isn't it logical that next time you'll put more large sizes than small ones in stock? Apparently, it's not logical at your place... Last time I spent almost 1000 lei on carpentry and I wanted 4-5 pairs of work shoes for me and my employees as work footwear. I couldn't find anything in large sizes! Thanks for nothing, and I'll buy from other stores and visit yours less often.
translated_English_Chinese: 用特别优惠和低价吸引人们，即使你们没有库存！！！商品库存应该根据销售情况补充，而不是其他标准。这样，男鞋的大码就会一直有货。补充销量多的库存是正常的，这样每件商品都可以随时供应给顾客。如果你注意到大码马上售完，小码却几个月都卖不动，不是很合理吗？下次你应该多备一些大码而不是小码。显然，在你们那里这并不合理……上次我花了近1000 lei买木工工具，还想为我和我的员工购买4-5双工作鞋当作工作服。但是我找不到大码的！谢谢你们什么也没做，我以后会去其他商店购物，少来你们这里。
translated_Chinese_Romanian: Utilizați oferte speciale și prețuri mici pentru a atrage oamenii, chiar dacă nu aveți stoc!!! Stocul de marfă ar trebui să fie completat în funcție de vânzări, și nu după alte standarde. Astfel, pantofii pentru bărbați cu numere mari vor fi întotdeauna disponibili. Completarea stocului de produse care se vând mult este normală, astfel încât fiecare articol să poată fi furnizat clienților în orice moment. Dacă observați că numerele mari se epuizează imediat, iar cele mici nu se vând deloc timp de luni, nu este deloc logic? Data viitoare ar trebui să aveți mai multe numere mari decât numere mici. Este evident că acolo unde sunteți voi, acest lucru nu este logic... Ultima dată am cheltuit aproape 1000 de lei pentru instrumente de tâmplărie și voiam să cumpăr 4-5 perechi de încălțăminte de lucru pentru mine și angajații mei, ca uniformă. Dar nu am putut găsi numere mari! Vă mulțumesc că nu ați făcut nimic, de acum înainte voi face cumpărăturile în alte magazine și voi veni mai rar la dumneavoastră.

text: Gasesti cu greu un angajat prin magazin, iar cand il gasesti te trimite pe tine sa-ti rezolvi problema. Exemplu: o pereche de adidasi nu puteau fi probati din cauza sistemului de alarma. I-am replicat ca nu se pot proba, deci nu se pot vinde si mi-a spus sa ma duc la casa sa le scot sistemul de alarma, in loc sa ia adidasii si sa faca el asta. A teebuit sa las copilul descult sa ma astepte, ca sa rezolv eu o problema care nu era a mea, ci tot a angajatilor, care pusesera prost sistemul de alarma.

translated_Romanian_English: You hardly find an employee in the store, and when you do, they send you to solve your problem yourself. Example: a pair of Adidas shoes couldn't be tried on because of the alarm system. His response was that it can't be removed. I replied that they can't be tried on, so they can't be sold, and he told me to go home and remove the alarm system myself, instead of him taking the Adidas shoes and doing it. I had to leave my child barefoot waiting for me, so I could solve a problem that wasn't mine, but the employees', who had poorly installed the alarm system.
translated_English_Chinese: 您几乎找不到商店里的员工，当您找到他们时，他们会让您自己解决问题。例如，一双阿迪达斯鞋子因为报警系统无法试穿。他说不能移除，我回答说如果不能试穿，就不能卖，他却告诉我回家自己移除报警系统，而不是他自己拿阿迪达斯鞋去做。我不得不让孩子光脚等待我，这样我才能解决一个本该是员工而不是我的问题，因为他们安装了有缺陷的报警系统。
translated_Chinese_Romanian: Aproape că nu puteți găsi angajații magazineului, iar atunci când îi găsiți, vă lasă pe voi să rezolvați problema. De exemplu, o pereche de pantofi Adidas nu putea fi încercată din cauza sistemului de alarmă. El a spus că nu poate fi înlăturat, eu i-am răspuns că dacă nu pot fi încercați, nu pot fi vânduți, dar el mi-a spus să merg acasă și să înlătur singur sistemul de alarmă, în loc să o facă el însuși cu pantofii Adidas. A trebuit să las copilul să aștepte desculț, ca să pot rezolva o problemă care ar fi trebuit să fie a angajatului, nu a mea, pentru că ei au instalat un sistem de alarmă defect.

translated_Romanian_English: In general, we come with pleasure to this location, but we miss the table tennis table very much where we had a great time and consumed some calories. translated_English_Chinese: 一般来说，我们很高兴来到这里，但我们非常怀念乒乓球桌，在那里我们度过了美好的时光并消耗了一些热量。另外，关于运动鞋的文章，特别是对于孩子（阿迪达斯），尺码38和39在一些顶级款式中都找不到，不仅如此。祝你们有美好的一天。来自康斯坦察的LUCA家族，怀着敬意和尊重。

În plus, în ceea ce privește încălțămintea sport, mai ales pentru copii (Adidas), numărul 38 și 39 nu se găsește la unele dintre cele mai bune modele, și nu numai. Vă dorim o zi frumoasă. Familia LUCA din Constanța, cu respect și considerație.

translated_Romanian_English: I recommend you to specify all the details at the return conditions, such as courier payment for returning the product. In stores, there is no return for swimwear, this detail is not specified anywhere. The sizes do not match, the swimsuit is very small, I ordered a product for 14 years and in reality it is for a child of maximum 10 years.
translated_English_Chinese: 我建议你在退货条件中指定所有细节，例如退货时的快递付款。商店里不允许退换泳装，但这个细节在任何地方都没有说明。尺寸不符，泳衣非常小，我订购的是适合14岁孩子的产品，但实际上它只适合10岁以下的孩子。
translated_Chinese_Romanian: Vă sfătuiesc să specificați toate detaliile în condițiile de returnare, cum ar fi plata pentru returnarea prin curier. În magazin nu este permisă returnarea costumelor de baie, dar acest detaliu nu este menționat nicăieri. Dimensiunile nu corespund, costuma de baie este foarte mică, am comandat produsul pentru un copil de 14 ani, dar în realitate se potrivește doar copiilor sub 10 ani.

translated_Romanian_English:
{"translated_text":"I don't know if my review is generally valid, but for the experience I had, I couldn't give any other rating. The quality of the service was less than satisfactory. Probably due to the lack of experience of the person who handled the bicycle left in the service, this impression resulted, but the result was not what was expected. For example: the transmission was wrong even though it wasn't necessary (resulting in unnecessary mess); the handlebar was crooked; it wasn't resolved even when I returned; the brakes were loosened instead of tightened; the disc brakes weren't centered properly; the tires weren't mounted so as not to have the ""8"" effect. All of the above were fixed by me, at home. The courtesy wasn't top-notch either, but not bad. Not to mention that this entire session was estimated at 140 RON... good thing the bike is still under warranty and I didn't have to pay. It can be better.", 
"language":"English"}
translated_English_Chinese: 我不知道我的评价是否具有普遍的参考价值，但根据我所经历的，我无法给出其他评分。服务质量低于预期。可能是由于处理留在服务中的自行车的人缺乏经验，产生了这种印象，但结果并不是预期的。例如：变速器出了问题，即使没有必要（导致不必要的混乱）；把手歪斜；即使我返回也无法解决；刹车松动而不是紧固；盘式刹车没有正确居中；轮胎安装不当，导致“8”效应。上述所有问题都由我在家里自己解决了。服务态度也不算特别好，但也还可以。更不用说，这次服务的估价是140罗马尼亚列伊……幸好自行车仍然在保修期内，我没有支付费用。它可以做得更好。
translated_Chinese_Romanian: Nu știu dacă evaluarea mea are o valoare de referință generală, dar pe baza experienței mele, nu pot oferi altă notă. Calitatea serviciului a fost sub așteptări. Poate din cauză că persoana care a gestionat bicicleta rămasă în service nu avea suficientă experiență, s-a creat o impresie nefavorabilă, dar rezultatul nu a fost cel așteptat. De exemplu: schimbătorul de viteze a avut probleme, chiar dacă nu a fost necesar (ceea ce a dus la agitație inutilă); ghidonul era înclinat; chiar și după revenirea mea, problema nu a putut fi rezolvată; frânele erau slabe și nu strânse; frâna de disc nu era corect poziționată; montarea anvelopelor a fost incorectă, ceea ce a dus la efectul „8”. Toate aceste probleme le-am rezolvat eu însumi acasă. Atitudinea personalului de serviciu nu a fost deosebit de bună, dar a fost acceptabilă. Mai mult decât atât, prețul estimat pentru acest serviciu a fost de 140 de lei... Noroc că bicicleta era încă sub garanție și nu am plătit taxa. S-ar fi putut face mai bine.

După ce am stat mult timp pe o bancă pentru a mă recupera, mi-a fost greu să părăsesc magazinul.

translated_Romanian_English: I would prefer not to exaggerate with trying out equipment (bicycles, scooters, etc.) it's not a playground.
translated_English_Chinese: 我更愿意不夸大尝试设备（自行车，滑板车等）的说法，这里不是游乐场。

text: Am vizitat raionul de biciclete cautand in mod special accesorii pentru bicicleta.Primul lucru care nu mi-a placut a fost lipsa etichetelor de la raft. Am cautat eticheta pentru un bidon dar a fost imposibil de localizat. In plus bidoanele erau complet amestecate pe rafturi.Acelasi lucru in zona de ciorapi pentru ciclism. Am cumparat la promotie ciorapi albi pentru ciclism la pretul de 13 lei perechea. Am luat si ciorapi negrii, de data aceasta un pack de 2 perechi. Pretul nu era afisat pentru acest pack. Am vazut ulterior la casa ca 2 perechi de ciorapi negrii costa dublu (44 lei) fata de 2 perechi de ciorapi albi, e drept, vandute separat. Dar am acceptat pretul asa ca va rog sa retineti doar lipsa etichetelor de la raft.Cireasa de pe tort a fost la casa, cand operatoarea de la casa a scanat accidental un produs (tablete pentru rehidratare Isostar) de 2 ori. Aparatul a emis 2 sunete de scanare (mie sunetele mi-au atras atentia) dar care nu au fost luate in considerare de operatoare. Dupa ce am achitat am verificat bonul fiscal si am constatat ca tabletele de rehidratare au fost introduse eronat de 2 ori.M-am adresat altui operator care a reactionat imediat si a acceptat reclamatia FARA a verifica insa produsele pe care le cumparasem. Poate chiar aveam 2 produse in sacosa...Banii pentru al doilea produs mi-au fost returnati imediat.In concluzie dezordinea de la raft si neatentia personalului, nu pot compensa zambetul contorizat la iesirea din magazin.

translated_Romanian_English: I visited the bicycle department looking specifically for bike accessories. The first thing I didn't like was the lack of labels on the shelves. I looked for a water bottle label, but it was impossible to locate. Additionally, the bottles were completely mixed up on the shelves. The same issue occurred in the cycling sock area. I bought white cycling socks at a promotional price of 13 lei per pair. I also got black socks, this time a pack of 2 pairs. The price wasn't displayed for this pack. Later, when I got home, I saw that 2 pairs of black socks cost double (44 lei) compared to 2 pairs of white socks, which is fair since they were sold separately. However, I accepted the price, so please note only the lack of shelf labels. The cherry on top was at checkout, when the cashier accidentally scanned a product (Isostar rehydration tablets) twice. The machine made two scanning sounds (which caught my attention), but the cashier didn't take them into account. After paying, I checked the receipt and saw that the rehydration tablets had been entered incorrectly twice. I approached another operator who immediately reacted and accepted my complaint without even checking the products I purchased. Maybe I did have two products in the bag... The money for the second product was returned to me immediately. In conclusion, the disorder on the shelves and the staff's inattention cannot compensate for the forced smile at the exit of the store.
translated_English_Chinese: 我去自行车部门，特意寻找自行车配件。第一件事让我不喜欢的是货架上没有标签。我在寻找水瓶的标签，但根本无法找到。另外，水瓶在货架上的摆放完全混乱。在骑行袜子区域也出现了同样的问题。我以每双13莱伊的促销价格购买了白色骑行袜子。我还买到了黑色的袜子，这次是一包两双袜子。这个包装的价格没有显示出来。后来，当我回到家时，我看到两双黑色的袜子（44莱伊）比两双白色的袜子贵一倍，这是合理的，因为它们是单独销售的。然而，我接受了这个价格，所以请注意只有货架标签的缺失。在结账的时候，收银员不小心把一件商品（Isostar补水片）扫描了两次。机器发出两声扫描声音（这引起了我的注意），但收银员没有考虑到这一点。在付款后，我检查了收据，发现补水片被错误地输入了两次。我走近另一位操作员，他立即做出了反应，并在不查看我购买的商品的情况下接受了我的投诉。也许我确实有两个产品在袋子里……第二个产品的钱立即退还给我。总之，货架上的混乱和工作人员的粗心不能弥补在离开商店时强迫的微笑。
translated_Chinese_Romanian: Am mers la departamentul de biciclete, în special pentru a căuta accesorii pentru bicicletă. Prima lucrare care mi-a displăcut a fost lipsa de etichete pe rafturi. Căutam eticheta pentru sticlele de apă, dar nu am putut să o găsesc deloc. În plus, sticlele de apă erau aranjate complet haotic pe rafturi. Aceeași problemă s-a întâmplat și în zona dedicată șosetelor pentru ciclism. Am cumpărat șosete albe la prețul promoțional de 13 lei pe pereche. De asemenea, am cumpărat și șosete negre, de data aceasta o pereche într-un singur ambalaj. Prețul acestui ambalaj nu era afișat. Ulterior, când m-am întors acasă, am observat că cele două perechi de șosete negre (44 lei) erau de două ori mai scumpe decât cele două perechi de șosete albe, ceea ce este rezonabil, deoarece erau vândute individual. Cu toate acestea, am acceptat prețul, așa că vreau să atrag atenția doar asupra lipsei etichetelor pe rafturi. La casa de marcat, casierul a scos greșit un produs (tablete de rehidratare Isostar) de două ori. Mașina a făcut două sunete la scanare (ceea ce mi-a atras atenția), dar casierul nu a luat în considerare acest lucru. După ce am plătit, am verificat bonul și am descoperit că tabletele de rehidratare fuseseră introduse greșit de două ori. M-am apropiat de alt operator, care a reacționat imediat și a acceptat reclamația mea fără să verifice produsele cumpărate. Poate că aveam într-adevăr două produse în pungă... Banii pentru al doilea produs mi-au fost returnați imediat. În concluzie, haosul de pe rafturi și neglijența personalului nu pot fi compensate de zâmbetul forțat la plecarea din magazin.

text: Mi-a placut ideea testarii produselor in magazin numai ca acum s-a ajuns in extrem. Se joaca tenis de picior, se lovesc mingiile cu capul, etc.. Stiu asta deoarece am fost lovit in timp ce ma uitam dupa niste produse. Apoi cel mic era la un pas sa fie accidentat de niste copiii care fugeau cu bicicletele pe culoar.Inteleg politica libertina a magazinului dar ma astept ca sa tina totusi lucrurile sub control. translated_Romanian_English: I liked the idea of testing products in the store, but now it's gone to extremes. They play foot tennis, hit balls with their heads, etc. Who cares if they hit other shoppers? On my last visit, on the main hall, two 'gentlemen' were playing football with their feet, kicking from items to visitors without any shame. I know this because I was hit while looking for some products. Then the little one was about to get hurt by some kids who were riding bikes in the aisle. I understand the store's liberal policy, but I expect them to keep things under control. I mention that I reported the incident at home, but I only got a 'we can't control people, try to be more careful'. What a shame...
translated_English_Chinese: 我喜欢在店里测试产品的想法，但现在已经到了极端的地步。他们打脚球，头部击球等。谁会关心是否碰到其他购物者？在我最后一次访问期间，在主厅里，有两位“先生”用脚踢足球，从货品到访客无耻地踢。因为我当时正在寻找一些产品，所以被踢到了。我知道这件事，因为我看到了它。当时小孩差点被骑自行车的孩子们伤害。我理解商店的自由政策，但我希望他们能够保持事情在控制之内。我提到我在家里报告了该事件，但我只得到了一句“我们无法控制人们，请尝试更加小心”。真遗憾...
translated_Chinese_Romanian: Îmi place ideea de a testa produsele în magazin, dar acum s-a ajuns la extrem. Joacă fotbal cu picioarele, lovește cu capul etc. Cine se îngrijește dacă lovește alți cumpărători? În ultima mea vizită, în sala principală, doi „domni” au dat cu piciorul într-o minge de fotbal, lovind fără rușine produsele și vizitatorii. Pentru că eram în căutarea unor produse, am fost lovit și eu. Știu asta pentru că am văzut-o. Atunci, un copil a fost aproape rănit de niște copii care conduceau biciclete. Înțeleg politica liberă a magazinului, dar sper ca ei să poată ține lucrurile sub control. Am menționat că am raportat evenimentul acasă, dar am primit doar un răspuns: „Nu putem controla oamenii, încercați să fiți mai atenți”. Ce păcat...
